            <tr>
                <th scope="col" style="justify-items: center;"><center><div class="info" style="padding: 5vw;"><br><h1>Senior Teams and FLL</h1><br><br><p style="word-wrap: normal; text-align: justify">Those who choose to be in Senior Teams (Most likely 6th, 7th, and 8th graders) get to participate in the FLL season which ranges from August to January. Each FLL season has a theme that it heavily draws from. There are 3 different parts to the FLL Competition: <strong><i>Core Values</i></strong>, the <strong><i>Innovation Project</i></strong>, and the <strong><i>Robot Game</i></strong>, which all may be familiar with.<br><br><br>The Breakdown:<br><ul><li style="text-align: left;">Core Values: The part of the comptition that involves key morals like <strong><i>Discovery</i></strong>, <strong><i>Innovation</i></strong>, <strong><i>Impact</i></strong>, <strong><i>Inclusion</i></strong>, <strong><i>Teamwork</i></strong>, <strong><i>Fun</i></strong>, and <strong><i>Gracious Professionalism</i></strong>, and your team's ability to show them.</li><li style="text-align: left">The Innovation Project: The part of the Competition that involves researching a problem based on the theme of the season, then demonstrating a solution to it.</li><li style="text-align: left">The Robot Game: The most fun part of the Comptition that involves building a robot, programming it, and testing its ability to complete goals on the mat. These goals are called missions and each mission gives you a certain amount of points.</li></ul><br></p></div></center></th>
                <th scope="col" style="justify-items: center;" style="align-items: top"><center><div class="info" style="padding: 5vw;"><h1>Sumobots</h1><br><br>
                <p style="word-wrap: normal; text-align: left">Sumobots is a fun and casual competition that we have every year after the FLL season is over. During the competition, all of the members come together and get divide themselves into teams. This competition starts in the middle of February and the final competition will be in the middle of May. Every team has 10-12 weeks to prepare before the competition. The competition is in a Round-Robin format where each team plays every other team in bouts. Each bout is comprised of three rounds The results of every round a team played are added up to a team's final score.</p>    
                </div></center></th>
